    <h1>My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic-Review</h1>
    <p>By: Gabriel Vincenti</p>
    <h2>What is it about?</h2>
    <img src="https://store-images.microsoft.com/image/apps.39377.9007199266242713.722a23df-5a2c-4d4e-921c-e7dbd059b123.f09d228c-e530-44bb-8c71-7ac4809eb5a5?w=672&h=378&q=80&mode=letterbox&background=%23FFE4E4E4&format=jpg" height=250 />
    <div class=what-is-it-about>My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic is a video game that was based on its television series.
       It revolves around franchise and the life of magical ponies that work together to create a happy and peaceful
       community and fight crime. The goal of the game is to build your own city; making houses, farms, parks, etc,
       and making it a success.</div>
    <h3>Who is it For?</h3>
    <img src="https://www.lifewire.com/thmb/-dvXO7ezItSPW-SjHURX92xH4c4=/768x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/GettyImages-717167227-5acaa26004d1cf00376d3de1.jpg" height=300 />
    <div class=who-is-it-for>This video game is intended for children. More specifically young girls. Although I believe
       teens would also enjoy this video game as it deals with a franchise, businesses, etc.</div>
    <h4>Platforms Available On</h4>
    <img src="http://photos2.insidercdn.com/XboxOne.PS4.112213.png" height=250>
    <div class=platforms-available-on>This game is available on multiple platforms such as xBox 1/360, Playstation 3/4, Nintendo Switch,
      and iPhone and iPad.</div>
    <h5>Is It Worth Buying?</h5>
    <div class=is-it-worth-buying> In my Opinion, My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, is a videogame definetly worth buying. The rating this game deserves is a 8/10.
        It is very fun to play. It allows you to use and enhance your Imagination. Although, there are always some cons to a videogame...</div>
